    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-01-09T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-01-09T13:00:00-05:00" n="283"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d283">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.5048/197a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-01-09T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 9, 1930—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1. Referring to previous correspondence on the subject of the International
                    Commission, please request of the Liberian Government definite information as to
                    the appointment of the Liberian member, when the Commission is to meet and other
                    collateral information. It is important that such information be furnished
                    before the end of this week.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
